overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with multiple
  issues, including failing Vercel deploys and critical security
  vulnerabilities. The assistant began by diagnosing the Vercel build failures,
  which were due to lint errors. Upon further investigation, it was discovered
  that these lint errors had already been fixed locally but not committed. The
  core of the task then shifted to systematically addressing the remaining
  issues from the PR review. This involved a critical security fix to implement
  HMAC-based session management for admin authentication, replacing a trivially
  forgeable cookie. Functional improvements included adding pagination and
  limits to API response and CSV export routes to prevent memory exhaustion,
  correcting PDF generation logic to accurately calculate sleep metrics by
  parsing minutes and handling empty time inputs, and enabling null values for
  optional number fields. The "Download PDF" button was made functional, and
  time input fields received robust regex validation in the Zod schema. All
  changes were successfully linted and type-checked locally before being
  selectively staged and committed.
